<p>The 64-year-old Golden Globe winner (L) told the LA Times: 'Everything is on Google, so I encourage you to Google it, about anything that I've said [about her]. I feel that that was then, and when I look at what's going on around me, I just don't have any regrets' (pictured in 2009)</p>

<p>'I feel that that was then, and when I look at what's going on around me, I just don't have any regrets.'</p>

<p>The two-time Emmy-winning actress and her husband Matthew Broderick will next celebrate the 18th birthday of their son James Wilke on October 28.</p>

<p>Sarah and the 58-year-old two-time Tony winner are also parents of 11-year-old fraternal twin daughters Marion and Tabitha.</p>

<p>Due to COVID, the married couple of 23 years were forced to postpone previews for their Broadway play Plaza Suite at the Hudson Theatre until March 19.</p>

